originalText.text: I'm very sorry for those of y'all who had a bad experience here but for those of you who have never been here, it is def worth to try!! For me, it is one of the best cleaning services in NY. When I was in NY for 4 months, I was committed to going there even though the location is not great (bc it's Harlem). But I always received the best quality work and the best service from them with affordable price. I even recommended my NYC friends to try this place. All of my clothes I brought to them were very pricey but they turned out ALWAYS perfect!!! Just please give it a shot!!!

originalText.text:
There are so many wonderful things that I will say about the talented team at Sky Blue NYC Cleaners!

I will start with the outstanding customer service at the front desk. Kasie is the BEST:  Friendly, professional, knowledgeable, and wonderfully pleasant with positive, welcoming energy. Kasie goes above and beyond consistently to always make your experience at Sky Blue a memorable one in the best way possible. The other front desk team members Dana and Heidi work extremely hard as well, and their efforts are genuinely appreciated.

OH EM. GEE. What more can I say about the phenomenal tailoring team at Blue Sky NYC?!?

I have taken several garments (summer dresses, shirts, jackets, work dresses) to their tailoring team and will continue to do so.  They totally get it. If you need a garment tailored, run—don’t walk—RUN to Blue Sky NYC and ask for Rosario and Charlie.  They are absolutely wonderful and love what they do.  Their experienced eyes miss nothing when assessing what needs to be done to make your garment fit like a glove, and they will make post adjustments on the spot if it is not absolutely perfect at pick up.

This is the excellence that you look for in a tailoring service.

Finally:  Shout out to Manager Darwin for building a business, service and team that is so needed in NYC.
Thank you so much!

originalText.text:
I’ve been going to Sky Blue for years now for all my tailoring and dry cleaning needs but on February 4th they went above and beyond.

I had an event that night at 7 pm. My own fault, but I decided to go shopping last minute and found the perfect pair of pants but the waist was a little too tight. I ran as fast as I could to Sky Blue to see if they could let out the waist a little bit in time for the event. They gave me two options and said they could both be done in time for the event. I’VE NEVER BEEN HAPPIER OR MORE RELIEVED! I left the pants around 3:30 PM and at 5:30 PM I got a text saying the pants were ready. The price was extremely reasonable for how short of a time frame I gave them. Extremely happy with the results and this experience has solidified my loyalty to them.
